(20, 38, 'Computer Vocab', 'Jonathan', '2016-04-20', '206868-binary-code-hacking.jpg', '<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>JPEG</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">: Joint Photographic Experts Group </span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Lambda</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">: wavelength division multiplexing</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Lossless compression: </strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&nbsp;A compression technique in which data is compressed and then then de-compressed such that the original data is returned that is no data is lost due to compression.</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Lossy compression: </strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">A compression technique in which data is compressed and then de-compressed such that the original data is returned- that is, no data is lost due to compression</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Multiplexing: </strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">Transmitting multiple signals on one medium at essentially the same time.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Multiplexor<span style="font-weight: 400;">: &nbsp;The device that combines/multiple input signals for transmission over a signal medium then demultiplexes the composite signal.</span></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>MP3: <span style="font-weight: 400;">&nbsp;A compression/encoding technique that allow high quality audio template to be reduced into a small size.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>MPEG: &nbsp;<span style="font-weight: 400;">A technique used to compress motion picture images or moving videos.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Run-Length Encoding:<span style="font-weight: 400;"> A compression technique in which a commonly occurring symbol in a data set is replaced with a simpler character and a count of how many times that symbol occurs.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>SONET: is an intelligent system that provides advanced network management and a standard optical interface.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>TDM: <span style="font-weight: 400;">is a method of transmitting and receiving independent signals over a common signal path by means of synchronized switches at each end of the transmission line so that each signal appears on the line only a fraction of time in an alternating pattern.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>WDM: is a method of combining multiple signals on laser beams at various infared (IR) wavelengths for transmission along fiber optic media. Each laser is modulated by an independent set of signals.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Channel: <span style="font-weight: 400;">A path or connection typically supporting one user.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Coarse Wavelength Division Multiplexing: &nbsp;technology for city and access networks. Transmission is realized using 16 channels with wavelengths between 1270 nm and 1610 nm. Due to the channel spacing of 20 nm cost-effective lasers can be used. The channel width itself is 13 nm.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Compression: <span style="font-weight: 400;">The process of manipulating data such that it fits into a more compact space.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Demultiplexor - <span style="font-weight: 400;">device taking a single input signal and selecting one of many data-output-lines, which is connected to the single input.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Frequency Division Multiplexing - <span style="font-weight: 400;">a technique for sending two or more signals over the same telephone line, radio channel, or other medium.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Discrete Multitone - <span style="font-weight: 400;">method of separating a Digital Subscriber Line (DSL) signal so that the usable frequency range is separated into 256 frequency bands (or channels) of 4.3125 KHz each. </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Terrestrial microwave - <span style="font-weight: 400;">A system, method, </span><a href="http://www.dictionaryofengineering.com/definition/technology.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">technology</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, or service, such as </span><a href="http://www.dictionaryofengineering.com/definition/multichannel-multipoint-distribution-service.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Multichannel Multipoint Distribution Service</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, which utilizes microwave </span><a href="http://www.dictionaryofengineering.com/definition/line-of-sight.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">line of sight</span></a> <a href="http://www.dictionaryofengineering.com/definition/communications.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">communications</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> between sending and receiving units located on the </span><a href="http://www.dictionaryofengineering.com/definition/ground.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">ground</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> or on towers, as opposed to a sender and/or</span><a href="http://www.dictionaryofengineering.com/definition/receiver.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">receiver</span></a> <a href="http://www.dictionaryofengineering.com/definition/antenna.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">antenna</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> being located on a </span><a href="http://www.dictionaryofengineering.com/definition/communications-satellite.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">communications satellite</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Single mode transmission - &nbsp;<span style="font-weight: 400;">optical fiber that is designed for the transmission of a single ray or mode of light as a carrier and is used for long-distance signal transmission. For short distances, multimode fiber is used.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Shielded twisted pair - <span style="font-weight: 400;">special kind of copper telephone wiring used in some business installations. An outer covering or shield is added to the ordinary twisted pair telephone wires; the shield functions as a ground.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Satellite microwave</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Right-of-way - <span style="font-weight: 400;">T</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">he legal right, established by usage or grant, to pass along a specific route through grounds or property belonging to another.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Repeater - <span style="font-weight: 400;">a device for the automatic retransmission or amplification of an electrically transmitted message.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Propagation delay - <span style="font-weight: 400;">the amount of time it takes for the head of the signal to travel from the sender to the receiver</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Piconet - <span style="font-weight: 400;">computer network which links a wireless user group of devices using Bluetooth technology protocols</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Photonic fiber - <span style="font-weight: 400;">new class of optical fiber based on the properties of photonic crystals.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pages</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pg 111:</span></p>\r\n<ol start="2">\r\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">2</span><strong>. How does crosstalk occur in twisted pair wire?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>Crosstalk occurs when electromagnetic radiation is emitted from one wire which is picked up by a second wire.</strong></p>\r\n<ol start="7">\r\n<li><strong> Why is fiber-optic cable immune to electromagnetic interference?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Because the information sent across the cable is sent via light instead of electricity</span></p>\r\n<ol start="13">\r\n<li><strong> What are the four orbit levels for satellite systems?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>Near Earth, Middle Earth, High Earth, and Elliptical Earth Orbit.</strong></p>\r\n<ol start="21">\r\n<li><strong> What are the WiMAX protocols used for?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>IEEE 802.20 is used for high speed data transfer and high speed movement.</strong></p>\r\n<ol start="28">\r\n<li><strong> What are the different wireless local area network protocols.</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>IEEE 802.11, IEEE 802.11a, IEEE 802.11b, IEEE 802.11g, IEEE 802.11n</strong></p>\r\n<ol start="31">\r\n<li><strong> What is the difference between data transmission speed and propagation speed?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>Data transmission speed is the time between successive bits; propagation speed is the time for one bit to traverse from one end of the medium to the other end.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Page 112:</strong></p>\r\n<ol start="5">\r\n<li><strong> The local cable TV company is considering removing all the coaxial cable and replacing it with fiber-optic cable. List the advantages and disadvantages of this plan.</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>Advantages</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong><strong>Lower cost in the long run</strong></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Low loss of signal (typically less than 0.3 dB/km), so repeaterless transmission over long distances is possible</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Large data-carrying capacity (thousands of times greater, reaching speeds of up to 1.6 Tb/s in field deployed systems and up to 10 Tb/s in lab systems)</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Immunity to electromagnetic interference, including nuclear electromagnetic pulses (but can be damaged by alpha and beta radiation)</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>No electromagnetic radiation; difficult to eavesdrop</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Disadvantages</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>High investment cost</strong></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Need for more expensive optical transmitters and receivers</strong></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>More difficult and expensive to splice than wires</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol start="7">\r\n<li><strong> Rank the following five media examples--twisted pair, coaxial cable, fiber-optic cable, microwave, and satellite-- in order from highest data transmission speed to lowest data transmission speed.</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">twisted pair 600MHz, </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Fiber, satellite, microwave, coaxial cable, twisted pair (satellite might be first under some conditions) </span></p>\r\n<p><strong>8.Using the same five media examples from the previous exercise, rank them in order from most noisy transmission to least noisy transmission. </strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Fiber, microwave/satellite, coaxial, twisted pair </span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n<ol start="13">\r\n<li><strong> How long does it take a &nbsp;signal to reach a satellite in low Earth orbit? Show the calculations.</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Time=distance divided by the speed of light. For a satellite at 300km, it will take one millisecond for the signal to be transmitted.</span></p>\r\n<ol start="18">\r\n<li><strong> What is one potentially serious problem with using your personal digital; assistant and Bluetooth to unlock doors wirelessly? Explain.</strong></li>\r\n</ol>', 'computer vocab, computer science, lossy compression, multiplexing,  MP3,', '4', 'published', 1),
(59, 1, 'The Benefits of Exercise', 'Johnny', '2016-05-05', 'hires2.jpg', '<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Jonathan Almawi</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Mr.Bayer</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">4/6/16 P.5 &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Benefits of Exercise</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">There are many benefits to exercising, such as a healthier heart, mind, and body. However there is a deeper meaning to &ldquo;work-out&rdquo; or in many cases to &ldquo;exercise&rdquo; . Just by staying active throughout your life, you are keeping your muscles strong. This includes </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">joints, tendons, etc to allow you to move more with less of a chance to get an injury. This is only just by having strong muscles and ligaments, how about your other parts? For starters, you are able to have better coordination and balance than a person that does not exercise. &ldquo;The more you exercise, the more calories you burn, that means, the more muscle you develop, the higher your metabolic rate becomes, so you burn more calories even when you&rsquo;re not exercising&rdquo; (This is a plus, if your schedule is too busy to exercise for long term, however you need to do &ldquo;warm ups&rdquo; to keep your body in shape). &nbsp;&ldquo;Another benefit of exercise is increase blood flow/oxygen levels to the brain.&rdquo; This then encourages the release of hormones that are responsible for the production of cells in the hippocampus, &ldquo;the part of the brain that controls memory and learning.&rdquo; The side effect of exercising, is a boost of concentration levels and cognitive ability, this helps reduce the risk of cognitive degenerative diseases such as Alzheimer&rsquo;s. Being fit may mean that the &ldquo;risks of colon cancer, breast cancer and possibly also lung and endometrial cancers are reduced. Studies by the Seattle Cancer Research Centre have suggested that 35% of all cancer deaths are linked to being overweight and sedentary.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You may ask what type of exercise I can do? For beginners you can do a &ldquo;moderate intensity exercise or vigorous intensity exercise.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Moderate intensity exercise</strong> <strong>definition</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;"> : &ldquo;</span><strong>Absolute moderate intensity has been defined by public health experts as any activity that expends 3.5 to 7 calories per minute. A classic example of moderate physical activity is walking at a 15-20 minute mile pace. Other examples of moderate intensity activities are: Brisk walking.&rdquo;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Vigorous intensity exercise definition : &ldquo;</strong><strong>Light intensity activities require the least amount of effort, compared to moderate and vigorous activities. The definition for light intensity activity is an activity that is classified as &lt; 3 METS. One MET, or metabolic equivalent, is the amount of oxygen consumed while sitting at rest.&rdquo;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>(</strong><strong><em>http://igrow.org/healthy-families/health-and-wellness/light-moderate-and-vigorous-activity/</em></strong><strong>)</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&ldquo;Examples of moderate intensity exercise include:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Brisk walking (100 steps/minute)</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Dancing</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Swimming or aqua aerobics</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Gentle cycling (5-9mph)</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Badminton or doubles tennis</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Volleyball&rdquo;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>&ldquo;Examples of vigorous intensity exercise include:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Running</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Power walking at 5mph or more, or walking uphill briskly</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Cycling faster than 10mph</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Aerobics</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Martial arts</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Competitive sports (football, basketball, rugby etc.)</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Skipping/jump rope</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Rowing&rdquo;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Work Cited</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">"Why Is Exercise Important?" </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Health Discovery</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Web. 06 Apr. 2016.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">"Fitness." </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Exercise: 7 Benefits of Regular Physical Activity</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Web. 06 Apr. 2016.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">"Why Is Physical Activity Important?" </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Choose MyPlate</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">., 27 Mar. 2015. Web. 06 Apr. 2016.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">"Light, Moderate, And Vigorous Activity." </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">IGrow</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Web. 06 Apr. 2016.</span></p>', 'Gym, benefits of exercise, healthy', '', 'published', 0),
(61, 1, 'As demand for African timber soars, Birds Pay the Ultimate Price', 'Johnny', '2016-05-05', 'Timber_logs_wood.jpg', '<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Jonathan Almawi</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Article Summary Assignment</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">9/16/15</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Mr.Kamper</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><strong>As demand for African timber soars, birds pay the ultimate price</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Demand for African timber increase, with that in mind the birds lose their homes due to legal/illegal cutting trees. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">&ldquo;Tropical forests are home to more of the world&rsquo;s terrestrial biodiversity than any other habitat, but are increasingly threatened by the impact of human activities. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The consumers want more timber in which cause the loggers to cut down trees. As a result the wildlife takes the most damage especially the birds that are living in the African Timber trees.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"> The bird that is taking heavy damage is Yellow-whiskered greenbul, its population has declined by 73 percent, and the icterine greenbul declined by 90% percent. Results further indicate that Ghana&rsquo;s forestry management system has seriously worsened due to widespread increases in logging , which has decreased or eliminated post-logging forest recovery.&rdquo; </span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The logging is taking place at a tropical forest in africa that is located at the northern part of the Guinea Forest. This logging occurred at early 1995 which caused minimal damage to the forest until late 2010 in which the damage was relevant throughout the area. The reason for this consumers want more land available for housing and to urbanize the area. Another reason is to harvest the timber to create commercial items such as paper, furniture and homes. Lastly it is used to make either farms for agriculture or the land will be used for a new mining operation. Before the logging ever occur the resources timber was bountiful with a diverse wildlife living at the area, however as of today many of those species are either dead or migrated to a new area to live at. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This article relates to me in a number of ways. The logging industry in Ghana most likely contributed to the toilet paper that I am using, or perhaps the wood became my paper that I used to make a rough draft for an assignment. However this comes at a cost of losing timber from the wildlife. It is best to make the timber industry at Guinea replant five saplings of Trees for every 3 trees they cut down. This helps with the ecosystem rebuild itself, this in return will help the birds to have a new home in the next forty or fifty years from now</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Vocab:</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">regenerate: regrow/rebuild</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Species at risk of extinction: A plant or animal species existing in such small numbers that it is in danger of becoming extinct.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Extinct: species, family or other larger group that has no living members.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Ranger Patrol: a person employed to patrol a state or national park .</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Illegal logging: is the harvest, transportation purchase or sale of timber in violation of laws.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Government: the governing body of a nation, state, or community.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Human activities: Based on what impact humans have done to their environment such as landscaping to their more suitable habitats. Such as making homes, farming, logging, etc. All of this includes biophysical environments, biodiversity, and other resources.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Science Daily QR code to the website</span></p>', 'Birds, environment, price, african timber', '', 'published', 2),
(64, 39, 'Impact of climate change on food production could cause over 500,000 extra deaths in 2050', 'Jonathan Almawi', '2016-04-20', 'Wheat-1.jpg', '<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Jonathan Almawi</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Summary Assignment</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">9/16/15</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Mr.Kamper</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><strong>Impact of climate change on food production could cause over 500,000 extra deaths in 2050</strong></h1>\r\n<p><strong>Summary:</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">&ldquo;Climate change could kill more than 500,000 adults in 2050 worldwide due to changes in diets and body weight from reduced crop productivity, according to new estimates published in </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Lancet</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">. The research is the strongest evidence yet that climate change could have damaging consequences for food production and health worldwide.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The modelling study, led by Dr Marco Springmann from the Oxford Martin Programme on the &ldquo;Future of Food at the University of Oxford, UK, is the first of its kind to assess the impact of climate change on diet composition and body weight, and to estimate the number of deaths they will cause in 155 countries in 2050.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">As global temperatures increase, the likelihood of a drought for farming will increase. With the trend of temperature increase 3rd world countries will take the biggest blow. Especially in water scarcity areas. Crop prices will increase around the world, causing tensions of economic value to rise/fall. &ldquo;The countries that are likely to be worst affected are low- and middle-income countries, predominantly those in the Western Pacific region (264000 deaths) and Southeast Asia (164000), with almost three-quarters of all climate-related deaths expected to occur in China (248000) and India (136000). On a per-capita basis, also Greece (124 deaths per million people) and Italy (89 deaths per million people) are likely to be significantly affected.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Education Relations:</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This relates to science because it is an environmental issue that deals with the agriculture of humans</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Body Weight</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">: &nbsp;</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">a weight that is believed to be maximally healthful for a person, based chiefly on height but modified by factors such as gender, age, build, and degree of muscular development.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Starvation</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">: suffering or death caused by hunger.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Climate change</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">: </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">is a&nbsp;change&nbsp;in the statistical distribution of weather patterns when that change&nbsp;lasts for an extended period of time (i.e., decades to millions of years).</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Death :</strong> <span style="font-weight: 400;">the action or fact of dying or being killed; the end of the life of a person or organism.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Researchers</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">: </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">is someone who conducts research, i.e., an organized and systematic investigation into something. Scientists are often described as&nbsp;researchers.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Crop</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">: </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">a cultivated plant that is grown as food, especially a grain, fruit, or vegetable.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Personal Relations:</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If the estimate are to be true, then I can expect food prices will increase around 2050. Unless something is being done this estimate will be true. Quite a number of people are starving already and its going to get worse if no actions are taken. My best advice is to make indoor vertical farming a widely used practice, or expect some serious population dips in the year 2050. I really have no words to explain this issue its quite relevant even today (Africa/other parts of the world including in Americas poorer cities and towns) Im pretty confident that well sort things out its not a big disaster or anything its just a bump that we need to handle properly or else it become an even bigger bump in later years.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Lancet. "Impact of climate change on food production could cause over 500000 extra deaths in 2050: By 2050, reduced fruit and vegetable intake could cause twice as many deaths as undernutrition." ScienceDaily. ScienceDaily, 2 March 2016. &lt;www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2016/03/160302204506.htm&gt;.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', 'environmental, science, food, production', '', 'published', 0),
(66, 39, 'Chapter 18/19 Answers', 'Jonathan Almawi', '2016-04-20', 'answers.jpg', '<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Jonathan Almawi 4/5/16 p.7</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>18 Vocab:</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Renewable energy: Is energy from sources that are constantly being formed.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Passive solar heating: uses the suns energy to heat something directly.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Active solar heating: Energy from the sun can be gathered by collectors and used to heat H20 or to heat &nbsp;a building.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Biomass fuel: Plant material, manure and any other organic matter that is used as an energy source.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Hydroelectric energy: As water flows across the land, the energy in its movement can be used to generate electricity.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Geothermal energy: The energy from heat in the Earths crust</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">1.Six forms of renewable energy are renewable energy(solar panels), passive solar heating, active solar heating, Biomass fuel, Hydroelectric energy, and geothermal energy. They all have pros and cons</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Such as solar panels are only functional when there is sunlight, same goes for the other solar alternatives. Biomass fuel output is not a lot compared to a hydroelectric energy but is able to reduce the waste by using the waste as a fuel source. Hydroelectric energy generates a lot of power, but it can impact the environment and residents that are living below the dam. Lastly &nbsp;geothermal could easily erupt if an earthquake happens, but generates power constantly.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol start="2">\r\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> The differences between passive solar heating,active solar heating, and photovoltaic energy.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol start="3">\r\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> The heat comes from the crust of the earth, this allow them to &nbsp;generate electricity using steam that rise through a well, later steam drives through the turbines in which generate electricity. The leftover liquid &nbsp;H20 is pumped back into the hot rock to be recycled again for power.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol start="4">\r\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Not all renewable energy sources comes from the sun such as geothermal energy that comes from a planets core.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol start="5">\r\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> A hydroelectric plant, this is due to me living in Illinois in which has a lot of waterways, especially the Mississippi River. </span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Here are some examples of dams that are near our area</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Dams are a clean energy source with zero emissions, the only down side is the cost to manufacture one and the environmental/social impact that it will cause. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Alternative energy:</strong> describes energy sources that are still in development. Some renewable energy sources that we use now, such as geothermal power.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Ocean thermal energy conversion (OTEC): &nbsp;</strong>In this system, warm surface water is used to boil seawater.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Fuel cell:</strong> Produces electricity chemically, combining hydrogen with oxygen from the air.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Energy efficiency:</strong> is the percentage of energy put into a system that does useful work. Energy efficiency can be determined using this simple equation: energy efficiency(in%)= useful energy out/energy out/energy in X 100.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Energy conservation:</strong> means saving energy.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Sec 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">CSP (concentrated solar power); power tower: lots of sun tracking mirrors (heliostats) direct the suns energy to a central tower where steam is made and then run through a conventional steam turbine generating station. Tethered wind generators: self lifting wind generators are maintained at high altitude in wind 24/7. Electricity is sent back to earth through the tether. Hydrogen could be burned in a chemical reaction /Hydrogen isotopes can be used in a controlled nuclear fusion reaction.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Eat less meat, drive less, unplug appliances that are not in use, and dont use the thermostat as often for temp in home, just leave upstairs &nbsp;window open.</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">With energy efficiency, you dont have to sacrifice comfort to save energy. Energy conservation involves a change in behavior to save energy (turning off the lights, powering down computers and electronic equipment at night, lowering the thermostat in winter and raising it in summer).</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Economics, if a person want to save money they could buy less meat, dont use heating as often/use other means of transportation.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Chapter 19</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Solid waste: </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">means any garbage, refuse, sludge from a wastewater treatment plant, water supply treatment plant, or air pollution control facility and other discarded materials including solid, liquid, semi-solid, or contained gaseous material, resulting from industrial, commercial, mining and agricultural operations</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Biodegradable: c</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">apable of being decomposed by bacteria or other living organisms.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Municipal solid waste</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Landfill: </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">a place to dispose of refuse and other waste material by burying it and covering it over with soil, especially as a method of filling in or extending usable land.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Leachate: </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">water that has percolated through a solid and leached out some of the constituents.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">1: </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">A material is biodegradable if it can be broken down by the biological processes. Plants, as well as animal matter are examples of something that is biodegradable, because it can be broken down and absorbed back into the environment.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">2: &nbsp;Waste disposed of from residential area is called municipal solid waste and waste disposed of from factories and manufacturing units are called industrial solid waste</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">3: waste is put into the ground and covered with soil with 2 environmental problems are the following methane and leachate.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">4: One advantage of the waste-incineration process is that it reduces the weight and volume of the waste. This process results in a less hazardous amount of waste. The gas and residue that incineration produces, such as slag and ash, is odorless. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">5: Computers and the TV screen as a monitor for my computer. They are non-biodegradable because they dont decompose as easily as an apple might be/plus their metals. Im not sure if theres any bio-degradable products for computers/screen.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Section 3 Review pg 535</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Wastes may be hazardous wastes if they exhibit any of the four characteristics of a hazardous waste (ignitability, corrosivity,reactivity, and toxicity) </span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Resource Conservation and Recovery Act (RCRA) is a US law that provide the general guidelines for the waste management.</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">One method is combustion or incineration. Another is placement in a landfill, land treatment unit, or injection well. &nbsp;Pro-makes jobs Con-some ways &nbsp;of disposing hazards may contaminate.</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Bacteria can be genetically engineered for many purposes. One such purpose is for the degradation of toxic wastes using metabolic pathways to do so. By engineering the bacterial plasmid, which is a circular strand of DNA and inserting extra genes, the bacteria may be able to perform tasks such as cleaning up an oil spill or breaking down toxic wastes. Once a bacteria has been successfully modified, after it reproduces by cell division, each cell thereafter will copy the bacterial DNA and the gene that was inserted into the plasmid also. Therefore, a virtual endless supply of these bacteria will result that can perform the desired task.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', 'env sci, homework, free answers', '', 'published', 0),
(67, 36, 'Ignite Outline Cards PwrPoint', 'Jonathan Almawi', '2016-04-20', 'mg22129524.100-1_800.jpg', '<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Jonathan Almawi English Proj &nbsp;</span><strong>Attention Getter:</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Climate change could kill more than 500k humans in 2050 worldwide due to changes in diets and body weight from reduced crop productivity.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong><strong>Background and Issue of the topic: Talk a little bit about how this became an issue. What are some of the consequences of this problem if it goes unchanged?</strong></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Climate change could kill more than 500k humans in 2050 worldwide due to changes in diets and body weight from reduced crop productivity.</span><strong> &nbsp;</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">As global population continues to rise, the food demand is predicted to exceed the supply. &ldquo;The Taskforce on Extreme Weather and Global Food System Resilience estimated that the population would increase by 1.7 billion by 2050 and would need more than 60 percent additional food production to meet the demand and prevent civil disorder,</span><a href="http://in.reuters.com/article/2015/08/14/food-climatechange-idINL5N10O4SI20150814"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> according to Reuters</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo; &nbsp;Technological advancements are keeping food production in check, but climate change continues to affect production due to floods and droughts.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Crop prices will increase around the world, causing economic, political, and social tensions around the world.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong><strong>Thesis-Main Idea of your speech</strong></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Global Temperatures around the world is rapidly increasing, and with each passing year farming is becoming more and more difficult to harvest the crops. Traditional farming used to be an easy and a productive task of harvesting crops, but now its becoming expensive and unproductive. Its best to get on the issue or else were all paying the price in the near future. &ldquo;The modelling study, led by Dr. Marco Springmann from the Oxford Martin Programme of the Future of Food at the University of Oxford, Uk, is the first of its kind to assess the impact of climate change on diet composition and body weight, and to estimate the number of deaths they will cause in 155 countries in 2050.&rdquo; With the trend of temperature increase 3rd world countries will take the biggest blow, especially in water scarcity areas. </span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong><strong>Problem(pull from 2 sources)</strong></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Statistics stating the extent of the problem(4-5 statistics, tell me WHY they are important). State significance. </strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Images in the background powerpoint backing up those statistics</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Make sure you hit on all the GLOBAL and DOMESTIC effects of your problem( can be one of your statistics)</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Solution (pull from 2 sources)</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Solution : </strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Make sure its feasible, describe it in detail</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Vertical Indoor Farming, is an efficient way to grow crops for the population. Indoor Farming is a soilless and sunless environment in which the plant hangs in the air with the proper light emitted to the plants preference of choice. On top of that Vertical Indoor Farming use less H20 than traditional farming, also vertical farmers dont have to worry of using pesticide, drought, or rough weather that may hinder the plants growth. The farmer controls everything more efficiently in a controlled growing area. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">According to Spread: &ldquo;Labor Costs were reduced by 50% due to full automation of the cultivation process from raising the seedling to harvest. We also have created a recycling, filtering and sterilization system with the goal of recycling 98% of the water used.&rdquo; &nbsp;By using vertical farming H20 consumption will reduce dramatically, this is especially good in water-drought areas such as California and Mexico (High producing crop areas).</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Personal Relations:</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If the estimate are to be true, then I can expect food prices will increase around 2050. Unless something is being done this estimate will be true. Quite a number of people are starving already and its going to get worse if no actions are taken. My best advice is to make indoor vertical farming a widely used practice, or expect some serious population dips in the year 2050. I really have no words to explain this issue its quite relevant even today (Africa/other parts of the world including in Americas poorer cities and towns) Im pretty confident that well sort things out its not a big disaster or anything its just a bump that we need to handle properly or else it become an even bigger bump in later years.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>____________________________________________________________</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Prob:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Climate change could kill more than 500k humans in 2050 worldwide due to changes in diets and body weight from reduced crop productivity.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Prepare for Tight up on water lid speech/</span><strong>prepare AI talk</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">&ldquo;The Taskforce on Extreme Weather and Global Food System Resilience estimated that the population would increase by 1.7 billion by 2050 and would need more than 60 percent additional food production to meet the demand and prevent civil disorder,</span><a href="http://in.reuters.com/article/2015/08/14/food-climatechange-idINL5N10O4SI20150814"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> according to Reuters</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo; &nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Technological advancements are keeping food production in check, but climate change continues to affect production due to floods and droughts.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Crop prices will increase around the world, causing economic, political, and social tensions around the world. </span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol start="5">\r\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> &nbsp;Global Temperatures around the world is rapidly increasing, and with each passing year &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;farming is becoming more and more difficult to harvest the crops. Traditional farming used to be an easy and a productive task of harvesting crops, but now its becoming expensive and unproductive. Its best to get on the issue or else were all paying the price in the near future. </span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol start="6">\r\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> &ldquo;The modelling study, led by Dr. Marco Springmann from the Oxford Martin Programme of the Future of Food at the University of Oxford, Uk, is the first of its kind to assess the impact of climate change on diet composition and body weight, and to estimate the number of deaths they will cause in 155 countries in 2050.&rdquo; With the trend of temperature increase 3rd world countries will take the biggest blow, especially in water