(87, 1, 'Persuasive Essay Outline - Colonizing Space', 'Jonathan Almawi', '2016-04-21', 'Generation-Ships.jpg', '<p><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Jonathan Almawi</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Ms. Fracasso</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">English III Period 6</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Date: 11/29/1</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Persuasive Essay Outline</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">It is in our best interest to preserve our species, by spreading our seeds across the cosmos. This will ensure that if one batch of &ldquo;eggs&rdquo; are destroyed then you will have spares to use. It is best not to repeat history such as the dinosaurs.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Space Exploration is vital to ensure our species continuum. Its the knowledge that enrich future generations to become productive members of society. Space exploration makes not only cultural change of our world but also economic, and perspective. We are only but a spec in this universe, our sun is dwarfed in size compared to a super-giant. &nbsp;&nbsp;In-order for our continued survival we must colonize space to ensure future generations have an ensured future, with the skills of physics, mathematics, and inspiration of discovering the unknown. Heres a couple of examples of NASAs contribution to society- Medical ultrasounds, enriches baby food/artificial limbs, Aircraft anti-icing systems and improved radial tires, Freeze drying, water purification/solar energy, and much, much more.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Were living on a spec in space that is orbiting a star, on this spec there are these lifeforms in which call themselves humans who are so sure that all the solutions to their problems are only on that one spec that they are currently inhabiting. In which they assumed the rest of the other specs that is around them should be ignored until all of their problems are solved on that one spec. Our species currently have energy problems on this one planet. While the universe have numerous ways of generating limitless supply of energy that we can obtain, people are fighting wasteful wars on resource that is abundant throughout our asteroid belt and beyond. Exploration will always come with danger, however in turn the rewards will be health, technology, and knowledge.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Only 17.647 billion (.5%) is spent on NASA , &ldquo;The 2008&nbsp;bank bailout&nbsp;of $750 billion was&nbsp;greater than&nbsp;all the money NASA&nbsp;had received in its half-century history&rdquo; (</span><a style="color: #000000;" href="http://www.openculture.com/2012/03/neil_degrasse_tyson_how_much_would_you_pay_for_the_universe.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Neil deGrasse Tyson</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">) &ldquo;NASAs annual budget is half a penny on your tax dollar.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">&ldquo;Football is also a very valuable tool for teaching its players morals&rdquo;. &ldquo;These three ideas are not solely limited to the field, they are also very applicable in the real world.&rdquo; The thesis with the skills of physics, mathematics, and inspiration of discovering the unknown. Space is not only an educational tool but also adds some sort of spiritual sense to some people and shows them how small our world really is, how much potential we have as &nbsp;species to accomplish in the times to come.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">In-order for our continued survival we must colonize space to ensure future generations have an ensured future, and if we hope to remain competitive in the world of technological advancement then it is the right idea to invest in NASA. Heres a couple of examples of NASAs contribution to society- Medical ultrasounds, enriches baby food/artificial limbs, Aircraft anti-icing systems and improved radial tires, Freeze drying, water purification/solar energy, and much, much more. &nbsp;We currently have energy problems on this one planet. While the universe have numerous ways of generating limitless supply of energy that we can obtain.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">Realistic solutions that will ensure our species as a whole is just to increase the space program budget by 1%, and this is due to the fact that the current budget for space is half a penny. If you increased to to a penny then you can expect changes to occur that will speed up production of new materials needed for space exploration, and at your living room. Another solution is cut the military spending by 5-10% and use that 10% for space exploration. This will have major changes and will definitely allow our species to explore the cosmos faster and ensure our batch of &ldquo;eggs&rdquo; are secured. If we want future generations to have a future then it is in our best interest to ensure that they have that future, and that future is in space exploration. It is in our best interest to preserve our species, by spreading our seeds across the cosmos. This will ensure that if one batch of &ldquo;eggs&rdquo; are destroyed then you will have spares to use. It is best not to repeat history such as the dinosaurs.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;">http://ls1tech.com/forums/racer-s-lounge/1524688-neil-degrasse-tyson-we-stopped-dreaming.html</span></p>', 'persuasive, essay, space, species, spreading, future, generations', '', 'published', 0),
(89, 35, 'Video Test x2 with Desc x2 Test', 'Jonathan Almawi', '2016-04-21', '', '<p><iframe src="//www.youtube.com/embed/14UQpIE7Igw" width="560" height="314" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>2016 Illinois Radon Video Contest : Radon the Odorless Killer</p>\r\n<p>Did you know that radon is the leading cause of lung cancer for nonsmokers? Radon can be found all over the world in any type of human infrastructure such as homes, schools, and offices. According to the EPA radon kills more people every year than drunk driving, fires, and carbon monoxide. Over 80% of home since the US have not been tested for radon. Radon cannot be seen or smelled and the only way to know that it is present at your home is by doing a radon test. &ldquo;Testing is the only way to know your homes radon levels. There are no immediate symptoms that will alert you to the presence of radon. It typically takes years of exposure before any problems surface. Radon is a national environmental health problem. The EPA estimates that as many as 8 million homes throughout the country have elevated levels of radon. For more information check out EPA website&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Links:<br />http://healthhouse.org/radon/il.cfm</p>\r\n<p>http://www.cdc.gov/nceh/radiation/brochure/profile_radon.htm</p>\r\n<p>http://www.idph.state.il.us/envhealth/factsheets/radon.htm</p>\r\n<p>http://www.epa.gov/radon</p>\r\n<p>https://www.youtube.com/user/ALAUMEnvironment</p>\r\n<p>http://news.psu.edu/story/339871/2015/01/08/medical-minute-radon%E2%80%99s-link-lung-cancer</p>\r\n<p>Radon video entry for Illinois High School Radon Video Contest of 2016<br />School: Plainfield Central High School <br />Participants: Jonathan Almawi<br />________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>Subscribe For more content!!http://bit.ly/1rSHNWC<br />Follow me on Twitterhttps://twitter.com/CyborgVillager<br />Check me out on facebook<br />https://www.facebook.com/pages/Theviiiager/57844284229152